Voc is significant to illustrate the execution of OSCs45 and reveals the highest value of current that can be taken away from an optical device in this context46. It is at the point of maximum voltage that can be gained at zero current value from any device. Voc depends on numerous features: external fluorescence proficiency, charge carrier recombination, light source, temperature of OSCs device, light intensity, and different environmental features. Principally, Voc relies on the saturation current and light generation that assists the recombination in the devices. Voc is approximately proportional to ΔE\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
